# 3. Technical flow

## 3.1 Request Intake → Governance

At the beginning, the request intake layer should call Governance before the Planner receives the request.

```text
User Request
   ↓
Request Intake
   ↓
Governance: evaluate_request_policy()
   ↓
Allowed? → Planner
Denied? → Stop / explain / escalate
```

### API

```http
POST /governance/evaluate-request
```

### Request payload

```json
{
  "correlation_id": "corr-123",
  "tenant_id": "tenant-a",
  "user_id": "user-01",
  "role": "business_user",
  "request_type": "enterprise_workflow_execution",
  "request_summary": "Generate invoice reconciliation workflow",
  "data_classification": "internal",
  "requested_capabilities": ["planning", "tool_execution", "memory_lookup"]
}
```

### Response

```json
{
  "decision": "allow",
  "risk_level": "medium",
  "required_controls": ["audit_logging", "tool_authorization"],
  "policy_version": "gov-r1-v0.1",
  "reason_codes": ["ROLE_ALLOWED", "DATA_CLASS_INTERNAL"]
}
```

This connects to your backlog item where intake is a governed request-shaping service and feeds governance context into the rest of the system. 

