# 9. Important implementation design

## 9.1 Governance calls should be blocking

For Release 1, Governance should be a gate.

```python
decision = governance_client.authorize_tool_call(task, tool, context)

if decision.decision == "allow":
    execute_tool()

elif decision.decision == "approval_required":
    orchestrator.pause_task(task_id)
    checkpoint_emitter.emit("APPROVAL_WAIT")

elif decision.decision == "deny":
    supervisor.evaluate_blocked_task(task_id, decision)
```

No tool/API/agent call should happen before governance authorization.

---

## 9.2 Memory writes should use an outbox pattern

Do not make execution fragile because a non-critical memory write fails.

Recommended pattern:

```text
Orchestrator
   ↓
Local durable outbox
   ↓
Memory write worker
   ↓
Memory service
```

But some memory writes are critical.

| Memory Write              | Critical? | Recommended Mode                  |
| ------------------------- | --------: | --------------------------------- |
| Plan version write        |       Yes | Sync                              |
| Task output summary       |    Medium | Async with durable outbox         |
| Checkpoint write          |       Yes | Sync or durable outbox with retry |
| Supervisor decision write |       Yes | Sync                              |
| Debug trace write         |        No | Async                             |
| Semantic memory update    |        No | Async                             |

---

## 9.3 Memory reads must be policy-filtered

Planner should not directly receive all retrieved memory.

Correct flow:

```text
Planner
  → MemoryClient.query()
  → GovernanceClient.filter_memory_access()
  → MemoryContextAssembler.compress()
  → Planner LLM / planning engine
```

This prevents leaking restricted context into plans or LLM prompts.

---

## 9.4 Every call must carry standard metadata

Every Memory and Governance call should include:

```json
{
  "correlation_id": "...",
  "tenant_id": "...",
  "user_id": "...",
  "run_id": "...",
  "plan_id": "...",
  "task_id": "...",
  "policy_version": "...",
  "data_classification": "...",
  "trace_context": {}
}
```

This is mandatory for enterprise auditability.

