# 10. End-to-end execution sequence

```text
1. Request Intake receives user request
2. Intake calls Governance: evaluate_request_policy()
3. Planner calls Memory: query_memory() + search_semantic_context()
4. Planner creates candidate ExecutionPlan
5. Planner calls Governance: evaluate_plan_policy()
6. Planner writes plan version to Memory
7. Orchestrator loads approved plan
8. Orchestrator schedules ready TaskNode
9. Dispatcher calls Governance: authorize_tool_call()
10. If allowed, Dispatcher executes tool/agent/API
11. Orchestrator writes StateCheckpoint to Memory
12. Supervisor reads checkpoints/run history from Memory
13. Supervisor calls Governance: evaluate_supervisor_decision()
14. Supervisor decides continue / retry / replan / escalate / stop
15. If replan, Supervisor writes ReplanRequest and Planner reads Memory again
```

